+ Authentication for git
-   Check authentication: ssh -T git@github.com 
-   Create a key for ssh access: ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C <your_email@example.com>
-   Log the output to your console and copy: cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub | cat filepath if not the one listed
-   GitHub → Settings → SSH and GPG keys → New SSH key
-   Recheck authentication: ssh -T git@github.com
-   Hi <user>! You've successfully authenticated, but GitHub does not provide shell access.

+ Config
- git config --global user.email <you@example.com>
- git config --global user.name <Your Name>

+ Create Repository
-   git init
-   git add README.md
-   git commit -m "first commit"
-   git branch -M main
-   git remote add origin git@github.com:Glyphix888/<repo-name>.git
-   git push -u origin main

+ Git commands
-   git remote -v -> View your remote
-   git clone <repo> -> Clone an existing repository
-   git add <filename> | . -> Add files for commit
-   git commit -m <message> -> Commit files to working branch


